[[Tammy Gambill]] |choreographer= [[Peter Oppegard]] |formerchoreographer= |skating club= Los Angeles FSC |retired= |combined total= 173.69 |combined date= [[2007-2008 ISU Junior Grand Prix|2007 JGP Croatia]] |SP score= 66.68 |SP date= [[2009-2010 ISU Junior Grand Prix|2009 JGP Poland]] |FS score= 116.91 |FS date= [[2007-2008 ISU Junior Grand Prix|2007 JGP Croatia]] |medaltemplates= {{MedalCountry | [[United States]] }} {{MedalSport | Men's singles [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[2005-2006 ISU Junior Grand Prix|ISU Junior Grand Prix Final]]}} {{MedalSilver|[[2005-2006 ISU Junior Grand Prix|2005-2006 Ostrava]]|[[2005-2006 ISU Junior Grand Prix|Men's singles]]}} }} '''Austin Kanallakan''' (born May 23, 1991 in [[Woodland Hills, California]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He is the 2005 Novice national champion. In his first year on the [[Junior Grand Prix]] circuit, he qualified for the Junior Grand Prix Final, where he placed second. He later went on to place 13th as a junior at nationals. In 2007, he came back from a disappointing short program to win the free skate and claim the bronze medal on the junior level. ==Competitive highlights== {| class="wikitable" |- !
